  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthen the management of water resources in water stressed regions by developing methodologies, tools, guidelines and policy advices to Member States towards the achievement of water-related SDGs</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">For many countries, water scarcity represents the most pressing challenge to socio-economic and human development at large. Water scarcity can be made worse by climate change especially in arid and semi-arid areas. To strengthen the capacity to manage water resources in arid and semi-arid areas, UNESCO will work with MS to develop methodologies, guidelines, policy advices. The activity will contribute towards the achievement of water-related SDGs, and other water related international agendas including Sendai framework and Paris agreement. Building on the achievements under 39C5, the activity will be implemented in coordination of G-WADI network, C2C and Chairs and close cooperation with professional organizations.</narrative>
  </description>
